  16,22,"Your Ilâh[2] (God) is One Ilâh (God - Allâh, none has the right to be worshipped but He). But for those who believe not in the Hereafter, their hearts deny (the faith in the Oneness of Allâh), and they are proud.[3]"
  16,23,"Certainly, Allâh knows what they conceal and what they reveal. Truly, He likes not the proud."
  16,24,"And when it is said to them: "